{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":2,"result":{"tools":[{"name":"medaka_check","description":"Type-check Medaka source and return structured diagnostics — the same JSON `medaka check --json` emits (stable `code`, `range`, `severity`, `help`, and a machine-applicable `fix` where available). Provide exactly one of `file` or `source`.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to a .mdk file to check."},"source":{"type":"string","description":"Inline Medaka source to check (no file on disk)."}}}},{"name":"medaka_type_at","description":"Infer the type/scheme at a position — the LSP hover, driven statelessly. Give a `file` path plus a 0-based `line` and `col` (LSP-style); returns the `<name> : <type>` at that point, resolving imported names against the project on disk. A position off any identifier returns a clean \"no symbol\" note, not an error.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file to query."},"line":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based line of the position (LSP-style, first line is 0)."},"col":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based column of the position (LSP-style, first column is 0)."}},"required":["file","line","col"]}},{"name":"medaka_symbols","description":"List a file's top-level declarations (functions, data types, interfaces, impls, …) with their source ranges — the LSP document-symbol outline, driven statelessly. Give a `file` path; parse-only (no typecheck), so it works even on a file with type errors.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file to list symbols for."}},"required":["file"]}},{"name":"medaka_definition","description":"Find the declaration that defines the identifier at a position — the LSP go-to-definition, driven statelessly. Give a `file` path plus a 0-based `line` and `col` (LSP-style). INTRA-FILE ONLY: it scans declarations in this same file, so a use of a name defined in ANOTHER file returns an empty result rather than a wrong location. A position off any identifier also returns an empty result.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file to query."},"line":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based line of the position (LSP-style, first line is 0)."},"col":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based column of the position (LSP-style, first column is 0)."}},"required":["file","line","col"]}}]}}
